main event: On November 13, 1959, a UFO sighting was reported by military aircraft that identified the object as a small silvery object, initially suspected to be the planet Venus.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 10-15 minutes., The object was described as small, silver, and round., The aircraft involved were from the 99th Bomb Wing., The sighting was at high altitudes of around 13,000 feet., Pilots reported the object maintaining a parallel course with their aircraft.
location: Approx. 560 mi East of Resolution Island, N/A, N/A
witness description: military pilots from the 99th Bomb Wing
